captions.text:
Hey Vsauce I'm Jake and since it's a new year
we should get some New Year Exercise .com.

Hopefully that will put you in a better mood,
a website filled with pictures of adorable

animals (awwwwwwwww) But those are only two
DONGs and I know that you need more...things
you can do online now guys.

This face substitution app uses your webcam
to fit and track a facial model onto you.

You can then swap your mug for someone elses
like Chuck Norris, The Terminator, Audrey

Hepburn or my personal face off favorite,
Nicolas Cage.

After changing faces, change channels with
My 90s TV. Just like My 80s TV that I featured

in a previous episode, 90s TV is a retro throwback
to the days of yore. There's channels with

music videos, cartoons, commercials and movie
trailers. Ahh, I could watch this forever

but sometimes you just have to Pause...Ahead
A game where you awake in an unknown place

with no memories. As the story unfolds you
use your pausing power to get ahead, but once
you do there is no going back.

And instead of using Pause use paws in CATlateral
Damage a FPCS, first person cat simulator,

where you walk around a room knocking stuff
down with your little cat mitts for two minutes
earning points.

or be a stealthy feline with Cat Ninja: The
Search for the Magical Energy Crystals an

incredibly fun platfurmer that has you avoiding
lasers, spikes, changing gravity, and cruisin
around with a jet pack.

Before you can become a ninja though, you
must practice in the Dojo of Death and endlessly
slice through enemies.

Replenish your energy with coffee and ask
yourself where does coffee come from. This

interactive site explains every step from
planting a seed, to where the bean belt is
located, to that final fresh cup of joe.

Now that you're refreshed, explore museums
with the Google Art Project. You can virtually

tour the Museum of Modern Art, the Acropolis,
The Rijksmuseum and many more.

After looking at all that art, create your
own with tentacles. Change the number of segments,

their length, and wave frequency to make some
pretty cool creations

or check out other peoples creations with
the Pattern Library. An ongoing project of

really cool patterns by different designers
that anyone can use freely for whatever their
heart desires

And then bring digital art into reality with
real life Emojis that replicate the ones find
on your phone.

If you can't find the right image to express
your mood, try the dictionary of obscure sorrows.

There you can find definitions for certain
words, some made up, but all of which based

in Etymology. Some even have videos to go
along like KETA, which is defined as: an image

that inexplicably leaps back into your mind
from the distant past.

Then discover the Origins of UI symbols and
the meaning behind them. The site walks you

through 11 well known symbols and where they
come from like the command symbol being a

Swedish icon indicating a noteworthy attraction
in a campground or that the USB symbol was

drawn to resemble Neptune's Trident...not
a man holding a bowling ball and briefcase
with an isosceles triangle for feet. *sigh*

Since you are learning so much you might as
well check out this music timeline and see

what music was popular when you were born,
and get some record suggestions while you're
at it.

Now let's listen to our new tunes while taking
a stroll through the gradient forest. Ah,

this is relaxing. Ah! I'm tripping out man,
ok this isn't peaceful anymore. I just need

Calm .com Choose your background scene, music,
and how many minutes you need, then sit back
and relax...

This is the perfect time to play one of the
most relaxing games, Second Amendment. A text

adventure game where you also have to control
the hand of the person playing and move their

hand to type. It's easy, you just have to..no...no...no..just
type the words. Why are you using your whole
hand? use your phalanges!

Alright, I'm sick of words so lets blow them
up with Font Bomb, a fun site that let's you

plant bombs in the text of whatever page you're
on and then all you have to do is wait...
boom.

But if you have to communicate somehow there's
the morse code translator so you can send

cool messages like this one that I got...and
then decode it

To get ready for human interaction once again,
join this conference call...... simulator

Or keep people from joining by getting a new
password at pass weird that will hopefully
be too repulsive for anyone to guess.

If your webcam is still on from face swapping,
use this webcam toy that mirrors you in all

directions so you can high five yourself,
or cuttle...fish. Colour Magician .com is

an interesting interactive experience that
tells you all you need to know about the Humble
Cuttlefish.

Then get out of the ocean and grab a friend
to play Robots are people too a platformer

where you and a partner share a keyboard to
get your robots to victory. If you're tough

you can man all the keys yourself or you can
go Mini Commando a short but really well done

point and click action game where you kill
Nazi's to rescue your family.

To go with these DONGs I made a new JAM, a
Just Awesome Music Leanback, for you over

on WEsauce so listen to that while you're
turning your face into Nicolas Cage's and,
as always, thanks for watching!
